# Backend Architecture Rules

## Package Structure (Strict)
```
com.workflowos/
  {module}/
    controller/   ← HTTP layer ONLY — delegate to service immediately
    service/      ← Business logic — all validation and orchestration here
    repository/   ← Spring Data JPA interfaces ONLY
    entity/       ← JPA entities — no business logic here
    dto/          ← Request/Response DTOs — never expose entities directly
    model/        ← Value objects, enums, non-JPA models
```

## Controller Rules
- Controllers are THIN — one line of logic max per method
- Always return `ApiResponse<T>` wrapper from `common/dto/`
- All endpoints must have `@Operation` Swagger annotation
- Validate inputs with `@Valid` — let GlobalExceptionHandler handle violations
- Never catch exceptions in controllers — they bubble to GlobalExceptionHandler
- Use `@AuthenticationPrincipal` to get current user — never parse JWT manually

## Service Rules
- One public method per business use case
- All service methods must have JavaDoc
- Use constructor injection ONLY — no `@Autowired` on fields
- Annotate with `@Transactional` where DB writes are involved
- Log entry/exit of important operations with `@Slf4j`

## Repository Rules
- Extend `JpaRepository<Entity, Long>` — no custom SQL unless absolutely needed
- Custom queries: prefer JPQL (`@Query`) over native SQL
- Never use `.findAll()` on unbounded collections — always paginate

## Entity Rules
- Always define `@CreationTimestamp` and `@UpdateTimestamp` on every entity
- Use `@Column(nullable = false)` explicitly — don't rely on DB defaults
- Prefer `Long` IDs with `@GeneratedValue(strategy = IDENTITY)`
- Never serialize entities directly to JSON — always map to DTOs

## Exception Handling
- Use domain exceptions in `common/exception/`: `ResourceNotFoundException`, `ConflictException`, `ValidationException`
- Throw meaningful domain exceptions from services — never generic `RuntimeException`
- GlobalExceptionHandler maps all exceptions to correct HTTP status codes

## Security
- Use `@PreAuthorize("hasRole('ADMIN')")` for admin-only endpoints
- Never log passwords, tokens, or PII
- All secrets come from environment variables — never hardcode
- Parameterized queries only (JPA prevents SQL injection by default)

## Testing Requirements
- Every service method needs a unit test in `src/test/`
- Integration tests use Testcontainers (real PostgreSQL — not H2)
- Minimum 60% line coverage enforced by JaCoCo in CI
- Test naming: `methodName_givenCondition_expectedResult()`
